RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY EVA was coaxed for the lead, having a slim advantage inside down the backstretch, began to pull away from the rival forcing the pace outside at the three furlong pole, opened up at the top of the lane and cruised home to the wire in a convincing fashion. FLOWERS 'N BERRIES pressed the issue between runners in the beginning, was throttled down to track the front twosome three wide outside of horses at the half, rallied three wide around foes at the quarter pole and won the duel for the place share, being a distant second in the end. I'M A BOURBON GIRL prompted the frontrunner three deep early on, continued to press the pace outside at the three furlong marker, could not match strides with the pacesetting winner when urged at the quarter pole and stubbornly battled with runners on each side to the wire holding for third money in a photo. CRUMLIN BEAST tracked the front duo on the rail down the backside, saved ground inching closer to the chasing rivals through the turn, battled for the place and show positions in upper stretch on the fence and just lost the nod for third at the finish line. P. S. RISING STAR trailed outside down the back straight, could not get involved with the field around the bend and showed a little interest passing a weary foe at the furlong marker. CRASH THE CREASE was off a step slow to begin, pulled the rider taking closer order to track the leaders between horses at the half, was roused for more to try to go with others five sixteenths out, made little progress through the turn and gave way by mid-stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FOXY LADY broke sharp to lead in the beginning, was relegated to track the contesting pair down the backside outside of rivals, at the quarter pole was ridden to go on starting to reach for more ground, swung out widest in the five path full of run in the stretch and went by challengers at the sixteenth pole to edge away crossing the line. HARD TO CAPTURE trailed the compact field down the backside, still could see the pack saving ground through the turn, rallied on the fence straightening out for the drive, angled off the fading leader on the fence at the eighth pole and dueled gamely to the wire but was second best on this day. GREEN GABLES assumed command on the rail at the five eighths marker, set the pace while pressured outside around the turn, put away the early speed foe in upper stretch, drifted inwards to the rail when urged right handed at the furlong marker clinging to the lead and did not have enough late to fend off the closing finishers in the final sixteenth. GIVE ME THE BOOTS prompted the pace outside down the back straight, shadowed the leader outside around the bend, bid for the lead bobbing heads up top turning for home and was on the wrong lead when tiring at the furlong marker. SOCIAL DRINKER stalked inside early on down the backstretch, took closer order to the leaders tracking on the fence by the half mile marker, closed the gap on the engaged front pair throughout the turn, loomed a presence in the four path at the top of the lane but faltered by the furlong marker.

VILLI OLENTO assumed the lead at the start, set a comfortable even pace unopposed down the backside, was collared outside by the eventual winner at the quarter pole and tenaciously maintained a slim lead down the lane but gave way grudgingly in deep stretch. RACE.FOOTNOTES: WICKENHEISER stalked on the fence having one horse beaten on the first turn, galloped along closing the gap on the leaders down the backside, was asked midpoint on the far turn, quickly swooped around runners by the quarter pole, took command at the furlong marker outside and was edging clear for the win crossing the wire. SHE MAKES A POINT assumed the lead getting to the rail on the first turn, dictated an honest pace uncontested down the backstretch, was headed outside by a rival at the quarter pole, battled gamely on the fence until the furlong marker but was no match for the winner nearing the wire. DELPHIA tracked outside in the first turn, offered mild pressure prompting outside down the back straight, bid for the lead two wide outside at the quarter pole when roused, had nothing more to give by mid-stretch and emptied out late.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUZ DE LA LUNA was under a hold sitting behind the pacesetter down the backside, waited comfortably keeping pace behind the frontrunner throughout the turn, pounced finding a seam in the two path in upper stretch, found another gear splitting foes by the sixteenth pole for the lead and was kept to the task to hold off the fast closing runner up at the finish. SACRED DANCER stalked between runners near the back in the early going, kept up with others travelling outside foes around the bend but could not find more turning for home and was unable to get involved driving to the finish line.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FASHIONABLY FAB was alone comfortably watching the pacesetter along the backside, closed in to press the pace issue outside at the three eighths marker, seized control by the quarter pole and drew away when roused by mid-stretch for the impressive score. TALK TO YA LATER trailed the field at the start, brushed outside foe into the first turn, continued to see the field down the back straight, caught up to the pack inside at the top of the stretch, split foes starting a late rally at the furlong pole and got up at the wire to nail second money on the line. TITO'S CALLING travelled in mid-pack on the fence in the first turn, closed the gap to sit behind the leader at the half mile marker, was roused with five sixteenths to go shifting off the fence three wide, loomed in the four path straightening out for the drive and gamely fought to the wire but was outdueled late just missing the place share in a photo at the wire. MY GIRL SKY stalked near the rear in the beginning, was brushed by inside rival entering the first turn at the seven eighths marker, improved outside horses down the backstretch taking closer order on the leaders by the half, made a brief run four wide around foes at the 1/4 pole to be in the mix turning for home and willingly ran on the the finish but could not reach contention. STREGA cleared the field easily from the outside to take this field into the first turn running on the rail, was uncontested setting the fractions down the backside, was pressed outside by the eventual winner at the three furlong pole, collared at the quarter marker, offered no resistance up front and faltered on the fence in the final eighth.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: O WOW was unhurried near the rear on the rail down the backside, crept closer advancing on the fence by the half mile marker, began to pick off runners sharply travelling inside through the far turn, shifted in to the rail when coming up quickly on a stopping early leader at the furlong pole and was very strong pulling away from rivals in deep stretch. MAKAYLA broke outwards on the start, settled in midfield by oneself down the backside, made a strong move running on the rail midpoint on the far turn closing in on the leader, shifted out pouncing in the three path to have a brief lead nearing the furlong pole, could not match strides with the winner late but held safe for second money at the finish line. BRIEF sat alone in the third flight in a strung out field down the backstretch, rallied three wide outside horses midway on the far turn reeling in the tiring frontrunner, was in the hunt four wide straightening out for home and finished up mildly in the last furlong to be a clear third at the line. TAKE CHANCES trailed the pack on the rail in the beginning, could see the field finding her stride down the backstretch on the fence, commenced a rally picking off horses inside with five sixteenths left to go and continued with momentum in the three path down the stretch to settle on the fringes in the end. MOON POOL stalked with runners on either side near the back in the early going, was ahead of rivals down the back straight, made no progress on the far turn and swung out to the five path showing some late energy to pass tired runners down the lane. SPEEDY JOHNY stalked three wide near the back on the first turn, improved on the outside three deep down the backstretch, was hard ridden keeping pace with some rivals around the final bend to be in range for a share turning for home, could not sustain the run and stalled in upper stretch. TOTAL BETTY chased the loose leader down the backside, was scrubbed on for more with five sixteenths remaining, offered little response, giving way on the far turn and backed away through the field at the quarter pole. BRIDGE TO NOWHERE bobbled slightly on the start, quickly recovered to for the lead into the first turn, set a brisk pace opening up on rivals down the backside, continued to roll on extending the advantage with three eighths left to go, emptied out in upper stretch and stopped abruptly at the furlong pole.
